Word reaching the Mgosi squad is that offers have been flooding in for red-hot Mamelodi Sundowns striker Peter Shalulile, who has banged in 21 DStv Premiership goals this season. ALSO READ: The loss reminds us that we are not invincible, says Sundowns’ MokwenaPhakaaathi understands that the club are, as expected, not willing to let go of their most prized asset.  “There have been a few offers for Peter, some coming from rivals on the African continent but most of these offers are from abroad.  “But none of them are enticing enough for Downs to consider selling Shalulile because what is the point for him to leave and go play in Scandinavia? If money is the problem, that can be easily sorted out,” said a source at Chloorkop.